section.def:
Authority
                (管理委員會) means the Security and Guarding Services
            Industry Authority established under section 4;

licence
                (牌照) means a licence issued under section
                21 or renewed under section 23;

licensee
                (持牌人) means a person to whom a licence has been
            issued;

permit
                (許可證) means a permit issued under section
                14 or renewed under section 15;

Secretary
                (秘書) means the Secretary to the Authority
            appointed under section 4(4);

paragraph.content:
the Chairman of the Authority, who shall be appointed by the
                    Chief
                    Executive;

the licence fee remains payable under this Ordinance as it then applied as
                    if sections 12 and 15 of the 2000 Amending Ordinance had
                    not been enacted;
